    "EWS should not only be about immediate alerts but also about providing data and insights that can guide long-term policy decisions and planning.",
    "This means developing systems that can offer insights into how different policy decisions might play out over extended periods, helping policymakers to understand the potential long-term impacts of their decisions and plan accordingly.",
    "among technical, domain knowledge, and community experts for understanding and validating the complex dynamics triggering displacement.",
    "Cooperation between national and international organizations, funding entities, and sectors like development and humanitarianism is vital for data collection, preservation, and innovative data-driven approaches.",
    "Encouraging collaboration among donors, humanitarian organizations, and academia can further transparency in cataloging predictive models, contributing to improved preparedness and response to hazards."
